Why I decide to become a PT coach ⬇️

When I first started I had no clue what I was doing, just like anyone who is clueless when they start something new. I knew breaking the mold of the old habits I built in the past was going to be hard but I always loved the challenge. I decided it was time to start educating myself and putting in the work. I fell in love with the process and within time, I saw my hard work come to life. I noticed so many people asking me how to do certain exercises or how I went from “this” to “that”. 

After 3 years, I finally decided it was time to leave my full time job to pursue something I had a great passion for. Thus came my online personal coaching business 🥂✨

It is the best feeling knowing I am helping someone live their best sustainable lifestyle and seeing my clients progress wins each week and entering a new phase of confidence 🥹

My 1:1 coaching application is available in my bio 🤎

If you find yourself feeling overwhelmed in a gym setting, this post is for you 🫶🏽

How to overcome gym anxiety—
Maybe you have never been to a gym before or you are going to a new gym location, this can happen in all stages of your fitness journey, this is totally NORMAL. 

⭐️ Remind yourself you are there for YOU. 
⭐️Create a routine for yourself so you know how to maneuver around the gym and if machines are taken, always have a backup plan! 
⭐️ Go with a friend! Having a friend to go with you will give you a sense of accountability & make you feel more comfortable in the gym environment. 
⭐️ Hat, headphone and hoodie combo has helped me zone out my vision/noise other than what’s in front of me. 
⭐️ Lastly, realize people aren’t really paying that much attention to you, so just do YOU. 

We have all been there at some point! 
I hope some of these will help you now or in the future 🫶🏽 Do it for you.

Week 3 with no gym—
I wanted to share some things that I learned with this time being away 💭 

1. Taking time allowed my body to rest/reset. 
2. Looking for the positives in situations. 
3. Focused on my 1:1 online business/focused on things I’ve been putting off. 
4. Not being so restrictive on food and just ENJOYING!
5. Allowed me to regain my passion for fitness not be so drained from a structured routine. 

As someone who is a workaholic and love to do the damn thang, it has been nice to slow down and enjoy more time with things I have been putting off. I always remind myself “what would I tell my client” with the position I am in. A spin off routine is weird because I am a gal that feeds off of routine BUT we will come back stronger and better💪🏽

Thanks for sticking with me 💫

HOW TO GET OUT YA FUNK 

Let me be honest…2023 has kicked my a**, constantly feeling like I am in a funk and not ever satisfied BUT I already failed having that mindset. So let me share some tips that’s helped me bounce back ✨

1. Moving your body
—even if you don’t want to, that’s when you need to the most, go and release some endorphins, get your body moving and HR up 💪🏽

2. Journaling
—Writing down your thoughts, goals, planning your weeks allow you to have a successful week when trying to hop back on track! Having your mind organized, you life will align as well. 

3. You are only as good as your mindset!
—you have to train your mind to be stronger than your emotions or you’ll lose yourself every single time!!

4. Take one day at a time
—everyday might not be good, some days might be better. Control only the controllables and stop thinking of all the things that might go wrong…keep your head up and keep moving forward 🤞🏽

I hope these tips help! Listen, it’s totally normal to be on a rollercoaster with your fitness journey, even I go through these funks! Don’t give up on yourself 🤍

How to fall in love with working out ⬇️

I hope these tips find someone well, these tips are tips that have helped me when I feel like I needed to realign my thoughts when it comes to working out…

1. Mindset change 
—instead of I “have” to workout change the narrative to I “get to workout” 
Remember it’s a privilege to move your body everyday 🫵🏽

2. Find a routine that YOU love
—maybe you don’t like bodybuilding, step into something that makes you feel good. Maybe that’s running, swimming, CrossFit, powerlifting, yoga, Pilates etc…

3. Wear something that makes you feel good
—when you look good, you feel good. If you’re one to get ready for the gym and that’s gonna motivate you to get there, by all means ✨

4. Have a good support system 
—the gym is all about you but having a great support system to help you stay on your sh*t & stay accountable is 🔑 

5. Just show up! 
—when you start showing up, results will follow. Once you see results, you’ll keep wanting to see more. So just keep showing up and enjoy the process 👏🏽

Do it for you, Kill it for me ⚡️

3 WAYS TO INTENSIFY YOUR WORKOUT ⤵️

1. Shorter rest time will allow your body to feel slightly fatigued starting your next set! 

2. TUT (time under tension) doing your reps at a slow and controlled movement will increase the TUT, making your sets more demanding.

3. By training with high volume, increasing the number of weekly sets for the same muscle group, allows an increase in hypertrophy! 

This is a great way to spice 🌶️ up your workout routine! Let me know if you want a part 2!!
